            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Section 10(23C) of the Income Tax Act 1961 exempts the income of educational institutions and hospitals that exist solely for education or philanthropy and not for profit. Sub-clauses (iiiad) and (iiiae) give exemption without approval where annual gross receipts stay within Rs 5 crore, and above that limit approval must be obtained under sub-clauses (vi) and (via)."
