            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Section 10(23C) approval is open only to educational institutions, hospitals and certain notified funds, while Section 12AB registration covers charitable and religious trusts generally. An institution cannot hold both at the same time and must choose one route. The Section 12AB route allows accumulation of 15 percent of income and a wider set of charitable objects."
